{
  "texts": [
    "The corresponding drug-target affinity measures, including IC 50, EC 50, K i, and K d, were available from DrugCentral, ChEMBL, and BindingDB.",
    "For all affinity metrics, the unit was first normalized to nanomolar (nM).",
    "Repeated measurements from different data sources and experiments were then aggregated based on the median values to reduce the impacts of outliers.",
    "The sign of drug-target edges was determined by the drug-target action type.",
    "A positive sign (+ 1) was given if the drug-target action had keywords including \"activator\", \"agonist\", \"opener\", or \"positive\", while a negative sign (-1) was given if the drug-target action had keywords including \"inhibitor\", \"antagonist\", \"blocker\", or \"negative\"."
  ]
}